🧠 Two Writing Regimes

1. Irreversible Writing (Typewriters, pen)

* Every word is committed
* Editing is costly / visible
* Thinking happens before output
* Errors accumulate → you adapt by planning more

➡️ Cognitive pattern:

Pre-compute → commit → live with consequences

⸻

2. Reversible Writing (Digital)

* Words are temporary
* Editing is cheap / invisible
* Thinking can happen during output
* Errors are erased → you adapt by exploring more

➡️ Cognitive pattern:

Emit → evaluate → refine → overwrite

⸻

